U.S. Cotton Production Will Rise Next Year, Informa Says

-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 
2011-10-14T15:38:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/u-s-cotton-production-will-rise-next-year-informa-says.html
U.S. cotton production probably will
rise to 18.473 million bales in 2012, compared with 16.61
million the government estimated this year,  Memphis , Tennessee-
based researcher Informa Economics Inc. said today in an e-
mailed report to clients. The Informa forecast is unchanged from
last month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Wilson in Chicago at 
 jwilson29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 